Class TestClass

java.lang.Object
cen3024c.TestClass
public class TestClass extends Object
Displays the requested nth value of the Fibonacci sequence using both recursive and iterative methods and displays the elapsed time.
Version:
6/7/2022.
Author:
Stephen Sturges Jr.

    • iterativeFibSeq

      public static void iterativeFibSeq(int n)
      Iterative method. Calculates and displays the nth term of the Fibonacci sequence based on 0 being the first term of the sequence using iteration.
      Parameters:
      n - Integer data type passed into this function to limit the Fibonacci sequence iterations to n. In other words, the user enters n referring to nth term of the Fibonacci sequence.

    • recursiveFibSeq

      public static long recursiveFibSeq(long n)
      Recursive method. Calculates and displays the nth term of the Fibonacci sequence based on 0 being the first term of the sequence using recursion.
      Parameters:
      n - Long data type value passed into this function to limit the Fibonacci sequence iterations to n. In other words, the user enters n referring to nth term of the Fibonacci sequence.
      Returns:
      Returns the values n-1 and n-2 from this method (recursive) resulting in the value of the nth term of the Fibonacci sequence.
